Marines among 6,000 who lay crowns at Arlington's graves
PFC De'Angello Robinson, 19, traveled seven hours by bus to lay a single wreath on the grave of a soldier he had never met.
For him and the other Marines who traveled from Camp Johnson in Jacksonville, N.C., to Arlington National Cemetery to decorate graves, it was a day to pay tribute to the men and women who once stood in their boots.
In a few months, from where we're being shipped, these could be us, Robinson said of the fallen soldiers.
