He was one of more than 6,000 volunteers who gathered Saturday morning to lay wreaths on the graves of veterans in various sections of Arlington Cemetery.
In 1992, Morrill Worcester, the owner of the Worcester Crown Company in Harrington, Maine, kicked off the event when he and others decided to decorate several hundred graves in Arlington Cemetery.
In what is now an 18-year tradition, Morrill and his wife Karen make the trip each year stopping in different cities along the way, to officiate events dedicated to military and victims of terrorism.
