Experts in the railway industry argue that only St Pancras International or Euston station offers such potential.
Lord Adonis will announce whether he thinks the scheme should proceed, but extensive public consultation and planning procedures mean that no final decision will be taken until after a general election.
Even if it gets the job done, the network would have to be built in sections.
